Scotland’s independent schools have a history of academic excellence, which continued in 2018, with yet another series of outstanding results in the exams, which were only further enhanced by individual and collective successes in sports, arts, music and other community-based activities.
With more than 30,000 students across Scotland, these schools, represented by the Scottish Council of Independent Schools (SCIS), strive to provide the best possible level of service to students and their parents.
The goal of independent schools is to prepare their students for the next and higher educational levels, the professional career they will choose and their position as citizens of the world.
As an educational field that can design and implement a school-to-school curriculum, we see that modern languages are still a popular and desirable elective course in schools.
Nelson Mandela once said, “If you speak to someone in a language that they understand, then what you say goes into their heads.
